The standoff entered into its second day on Tuesday, with asylum seekers camping on the Belarusian side of the border overnight. According to Polish estimates, up to 4,000 people remain at the border, with the largest group amassed near the Kuznica-Bruzhi border crossing. Some 10,000 more migrants are believed to be elsewhere in Belarus, heading toward the border to try and get into the EU. Poland deployed additional police and troops, as well as assorted military hardware as the migrants tried to take the border by storm, cutting through razor wire and felling trees onto it. Sytuacja na granicy polsko-biaÅ‚oruskiej. Mamy do czynienia ze zorganizowanym niszczeniem umocnieÅ„ granicznych. Dochodzi rÃ³wnieÅ¼ do bezpoÅ›rednich atakÃ³w na polskich funkcjonariuszy StraÅ¼y Granicznej, Policji oraz Å¼oÅ‚nierzy. wideo cz.1 pic.twitter.com/ueSs212tmpâ€” Piotr MÃ¼ller (@PiotrMuller) November 8, 2021 Sytuacja na granicy polsko-biaÅ‚oruskiej. Mamy do czynienia ze zorganizowanym niszczeniem umocnieÅ„ granicznych. Dochodzi rÃ³wnieÅ¼ do bezpoÅ›rednich atakÃ³w na polskich funkcjonariuszy StraÅ¼y Granicznej, Policji oraz Å¼oÅ‚nierzy. wideo cz.1 pic.twitter.com/ueSs212tmp Top Polish authorities said the amassment of troops was absolutely necessary to defend the country and the EU as a whole from the â€œattackâ€ by the Belarusian â€œregime.â€ â€œWe currently have a camp of migrants who are blocked from the Belarusian side. There are about 1,000 people there, mostly young men. These are aggressive actions that we must repel, fulfilling our obligations as a member of the European Union,â€ Polish President Andrzej Duda said on Tuesday. Min. @mblaszczak w #Sejm: PowinniÅ›my byÄ‡ dozgonnie wdziÄ™czni naszym Å¼oÅ‚nierzom i funkcjonariuszom, za ktÃ³rymi juÅ¼ kilka miesiÄ™cy niesamowicie ciÄ™Å¼kiej sÅ‚uÅ¼by, a przed nimi kolejne. Oni muszÄ… czuÄ‡ nasze wsparcie, muszÄ… wiedzieÄ‡, Å¼e stoi za nimi caÅ‚y NarÃ³d. pic.twitter.com/3rGCqPomCPâ€” Ministerstwo Obrony Narodowej ğŸ‡µğŸ‡± (@MON_GOV_PL) N